      "  KAN-AE-Combined-E               AUC = 96.26%\n",
      "  LIME-Weighted-Recon             AUC = 94.61%\n",
      "  KAN-AE-Symbolic-D               AUC = 75.34%\n",
      "\n",
      "Interpretation:\n",
      "  SHAP/LIME produce a global importance weighting of reconstruction error.\n",
      "  Score D uses per-sample symbolic equation violations — equation-level attribution.\n",
      "  Score D advantages over SHAP/LIME in this benchmark:\n",
      "    • Interpretable at inference time without re-running the explainer\n",
      "    • Pinpoints which health equation failed, not just which feature matters globally\n",
      "    • Calibrated tolerance bands from training data (R²-weighted deadband)\n"
